President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey Bossert Clark as the Assistant Attorney General, Environment and Natural Resources at the Department of Justice. Clark is a partner at Kirkland & Ellis LLP and has extensive experience in administrative law. He has worked on significant cases and argued and won numerous cases in multiple Circuits. Clark also served as the Deputy Assistant Attorney General for the Environment and Natural Resources Division of the Justice Department from 2001 to 2005.

Ryan McCarthy has been nominated to be the Under Secretary of the Army. McCarthy previously served as the Vice President of the Sustainment Program for the F-35 program at Lockheed Martin. He implemented the restructuring and organizational redesign of the sustainment line of business. McCarthy has also held various roles on the F-35 Program and at the Corporate Office of Lockheed Martin. He served as a Special Assistant to Secretary of Defense Robert Gates and has experience in the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on International Relations and the private sector.

President Trump also announced the continuation of Dr. Francis Collins as the Director of the National Institutes of Health. Dr. Collins is a physician-geneticist known for his discoveries of disease genes and his leadership of the Human Genome Project. He has served as the director of the National Human Genome Research Institute at NIH from 1993 to 2008 and has been the NIH Director since 2009. Dr. Collins is a member of prestigious scientific academies and has received awards such as the Presidential Medal of Freedom and the National Medal of Science.